text.tspan: Terms and Conditions
The ­promoter of the game is BanglaCAT, the authorized distributor of
Caterpillar Inc. USA in Bangladesh, whose registered offce is at Road-11,
Plot- 68, Block-H, Banani, Dhaka-1213, Bangladesh.
Entry into the game is open for all & will be made public.
There is no entry fee and no purchase necessary to qualify for entry.
To enter the game, participants will need to have a genuine profle in
Facebook, as the game can only be accessed & played from Facebook.
The game will run infnite period & will only come to an end when the
promoter of the game, BanglaCAT, wishes to. The reason of keeping the
game open on infnite period is bound with the objective of the game, that
is to cultivate and improve cultural, historical, and socio-economic
knowledge of Bangladesh. Hence, the game is built for Bangladeshi
citizen or nationalities regardless of the present place of residence.
BanglaCAT holds the sole right to reward participants as per the
formation of the game.
BanglaCAT will set and announce the reward scheme as it is under their
discretion.
Rewarded participants will be announced on the Facebook page of
“Bangla Cat” and subsequently, the authority will contact the concerned
participants by phone and e-mail.
No cash alternative to the prizes will be offered. The prizes are not
transferable. BanglaCAT reserves the right to substitute the prize with
any other prize of equal value to the prize offered herein, at its sole
discretion.
A participant is entitled to receive reward or prize as set by the promoter
of the game, BanglaCAT, once. Yet, the participant can play the game on
infnite occasions.
Any decision taken by BanglaCAT is fnal and binding and BanglaCAT
shall not enter into any correspondence about the result.
By entering this game you agree to be bound by these terms and
conditions. Any breach of the terms and conditions may, at BanglaCAT’s
absolute discretion, result in forfeiture of any prize or disqualifcation
from the game.
